The paper discusses a security threat related to password-based authentication techniques and proposes a new approach to mitigate it. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The proposed approach involves generating honeywords, which is a technique related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the storage overhead of existing schemes, which is a concern in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
